{CritterProperty::NCRKarlsonSon}{2}{According to the sergeant, Karlson's son swiped a pistol from one of the Rangers and won't admit where he hid it.}
{CritterProperty::NCRKarlsonSon}{3}{Karlson's son has the pistol. Don't lose sight of the boy. Make him understand he's in your hands and can't get away.}
{CritterProperty::NCRKarlsonSon}{4}{You couldn't catch up with the boy. He won't give up the pistol.}
{CritterProperty::NCRKarlsonSon}{5}{You stayed right on Karlson's son's heels. Walk up to him and take the pistol.}
{CritterProperty::NCRKarlsonSon}{6}{You have the pistol the president's boy swiped. Tell the sergeant about the find.}
{CritterProperty::NCRKarlsonSon}{7}{You didn't admit to the sergeant that you took the pistol from Karlson's son.}
{CritterProperty::NCRKarlsonSon}{8}{You gave the pistol to the sergeant. Return to President Karlson.}
{CritterProperty::NCRKarlsonSon}{9}{You fulfilled Karlson's request.}

